I found the deserialization trap: `CommandStatus` is exposing the core `AgentState`/`AgentHistory` types, but those aren’t safely round-trippable through Jackson because `AgentState` requires an ignored `browserUseState`. The clean fix is to switch the REST payload to a small, REST-specific agent-state/history DTO and map into it in `toCommandStatus()`.

